HEADWORD: Altiscope
<hw>Al"ti*scope</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>altus</ets> high + Gr. <?/ to view.]</ety> <def>An arrangement of
lenses and mirrors which enables a person to see an object in spite of
intervening objects. Since the early 1900's, most commonly called
<er>periscope</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

